name: Magpie Goose
rangeDescription: Trans-fly savanna of southern new guinea and coastal northern australia
description: Large black-and-white waterbird with bulbous lump on the top of its head and striking orange legs and feet. Often seen in very large, noisy flocks.

name: Red-chested Buttonquail
rangeDescription: Savanna and scrub of northern and eastern australia
description: Small, dark, secretive buttonquail with pale eye, found in dense grassland habitats, where most commonly observed exploding from cover and flying rapidly away. In flight, note the fairly uniformly dark upperparts, with less contrast between flight feathers and coverts than in most other buttonquail.

name: Rufous-backed Antvireo
rangeDescription: Coastal mountains of southeastern brazil (rio de janeiro to paraná)
description: Big headed antbird with a heavy hooked bill and a shortish tail. Rufous above and pale below with a gray neck and face dappled with white spots.

name: Russet-naped Wren
rangeDescription: Arid lowlands of southwestern mexico (colima and southern jalisco to western chiapas)
description: Large wren usually found in small groups, less often in pairs. Mainly found in thorn forest and dry scrubby habitats.

name: Little Bunting
rangeDescription: Taiga of northern eurasia; winters to india, southeastern asia, and philippines
description: Small bunting with an attractive contrasting head pattern: black crown with red-brown central stripe and pale eyering. Rufous cheeks bordered by narrow black lines framing the eyes.

name: Hispaniolan Trogon
rangeDescription: Montane forest of hispaniola; locally in coastal mangroves
description: This strikingly colored denizen of montane woodlands (and less often, mangrove swamps) is rather sedate. It is often found sitting upright and rather motionless, typically in pairs.

name: Tboli Sunbird
rangeDescription: Southern philippines (mountains of southern mindanao)
description: A small, localized bird of montane forest in southern Mindanao. Has a long, curved bill, a gray head, yellow underparts and rump, an olive back and wings, and a white-tipped tail.

name: Trilling Tapaculo
rangeDescription: Andes of northwestern peru to east-central bolivia (santa cruz)
description: Tiny, compact gray bird. Females are slightly duller, with brown lower sides and rump.

name: Giant Coot
rangeDescription: Andes of southern peru to northern chile and northwestern argentina
description: Distinctive huge coot of lakes and bogs in high Andes. Often seen standing along shorelines or on big weed-matted nest mounds.

name: Sombre Pigeon
rangeDescription: Humid montane forest of sulawesi
description: A distinctive, very large gray pigeon with a small patch of red skin around the eye and a barred belly and undertail. Back blackish-gray, head and breast much paler gray.

name: Bougainville Crow
rangeDescription: Bougainville and shortland (northwestern solomon islands)
description: A medium-sized entirely black crow with bluish gloss on the head and purple gloss on the upperparts. Bill very large with a strongly arched top edge.

name: Adamawa Turtle-Dove
rangeDescription: Highlands of eastern nigeria, northern cameroon, and far southwestern chad
description: A dark turtle-dove with typical scaly rufous-pink edging to the wings and black patches on the sides of the neck. The face is pale silvery-gray and the belly and flanks are pinkish-mauve.

name: Japanese Robin
rangeDescription: Breeds on southern sakhalin island, the southern kuril islands, and japan; winters in southeastern china (northwestern fujian southward to guangdong and guangxi)
description: Small migratory songbird of mature forest with distinctive orange breast and dull brown upperparts. Sticks to undergrowth in both montane breeding grounds and lowland wintering grounds, though presence in the former may be given away by its loud song: a trill following a single introductory note.

name: Ultramarine Kingfisher
rangeDescription: Eastern and central solomon islands
description: A distinctive medium-sized blue-and-white kingfisher with a prominent dark mask, blue crown, bright white neck and underparts, blue wings and back, and reddish undertail. Male has a white rump.
imageCreditName: Lars Petersson | My World of Bird Photography

name: Sula Scops-Owl
rangeDescription: Sula islands (taliabu, seho, mangole, and sanana)
description: A small brown owl with indistinct ear tufts (often not visible) and yellow irises. Largely brown, mottled with dark streaks and markings over much of the body, with pale and white markings on the wings.

name: Carruthers's Cisticola
rangeDescription: Democratic republic of the congo to uganda, western kenya, rwanda, burundi, and northwestern tanzania
description: Relatively colorful, mid-sized, long-tailed cisticola. Note the gray-brown back with thick black streaks, rufous on the wing and cap, and whitish underparts.

name: Black-billed Hanging-Parrot
rangeDescription: Sulu archipelago (bongao, jolo, and tawitawi)
description: A very small forest parrot endemic to the Sulu Archipelago. Overall green in color with a red forehead and rump, a dark bill, orange legs, and a small orange patch on the back of the head.

name: Tristram's Storm-Petrel
rangeDescription: Breeds and ranges hawaii, izu, and volcano islands
description: Dark brown, fork-tailed seabird of the northwestern and central Pacific, where it breeds on Japanese and Hawaiian islands. Generally forages far offshore and does not associate with boats.

name: Violet-capped Woodnymph
rangeDescription: Southeastern brazil to eastern paraguay and northeastern argentina
description: Common hummingbird of both montane and lowland forests and woodlands. Also visits feeders and gardens.

name: Saffron Toucanet
rangeDescription: Humid forest of southeastern brazil to northeastern argentina and eastern paraguay
description: Unmistakable yellow toucan with a long two-toned bill: half red and half greenish-yellow. The iris is pale and framed with bare red skin.
